The paper discusses existential rules in the context of Ontology-Based Data Access, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the chase algorithm, which is a common algorithm used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for reasoning with knowledge bases. The paper also discusses acyclicity conditions, which are a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses nonmonotonic negation, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and in description logics (cs.DL).
